name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: The Rock Church - 1901 7th Avenue SE, Olympia WA, 98501
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a Pfizer clinic being held at Rock Church, 1901 7th Avenue SE, Olympia WA, 98501 from 4 - 6PM. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with warm layers. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Sacred Heart Catholic Church - 812 Bowker st SE, Lacey WA, 98503
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

This is a walk-in clinic at Sacred Heart Catholic Church - 812 Bowker St SE, Lacey, WA 98503 for anyone age 12 and older from 9am-4pm. All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
